gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 133, Timberwolves 115
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns defeated the Timberwolves, 133-115. Devin Booker recorded 31 points, five assists, and four rebounds for the Suns, with Kevin Durant adding 31 points, six rebounds, and six assists in the victory. Karl-Anthony Towns tallied 25 points, seven rebounds, and two assists for the Timberwolves in the losing effort. The Sun improve to 5-6 on the season, while the Timberwolves fall to 8-3.
